‘Work event’

On 12 January Mr Johnson said: “I believed implicitly that this was a work event, but with hindsight, I should have sent everyone back inside”

‘All guidance was followed'

The government has ignored calls from parliamentary committees to create an appeal process that would stop innocent people having to risk prosecution to defend themselves
🔴 The numbers, which include all Covid prosecutions finalised between March 2020 and the end of February, are likely to rise as more cases go to court 📈

🔴 Every single one of the 311 charges brought under the separate Coronavirus Act were wrongful, because criminal offences under the law only apply to “potentially infectious persons” and it was misapplied by police forces
🔴 The figure includes 528 of over 2,500 prosecutions under the Health Protection Regulations, which were the laws broken by politicians and civil servants fined over Downing Street parties

"This isn't to prove that trans women can't be great athletes, or win, or even dominate. It is to prove that people are lying to you in order to turn you against trans women athletes," said Schuyler Bailar, the first openly trans swimmer in the NCAA men’s first division.

Yet numbers can only tell us so much. 

Trans advocates argue that even if trans women were winning more competitions, that would not prove they had an unfair advantage, nor would it justify their exclusion from women's events.

These statistics seem largely in line with those of trans athletes across the world. 

Although trans women have been allowed to compete in women's Olympics since 2004, none have won a medal.

Breakdown:

🔴 Thomas won her race – but didn’t break records

🔴 Her swimming times are on par with cis women

Yet in all this, there has been scant detail about how Ms Thomas's performance actually compares to other women at her level. 

@Independent crunched the numbers – and found little evidence that she poses any threat to women's sport.

Florida's Republican governor Ron DeSantis, who last year approved legislation banning trans women from high school and college women's sports, even signed a proclamation on Tuesday declaring 500-yard runner-up Emma Weyant the "rightful winner".
Amid her success, though, Ms Thomas has become a lightning rod in the debate about trans women in sport, as well as a target for much of the American right.
On 17 March, Lia Thomas became the first openly transgender athlete to win America's top trophy in university sports when she swam to victory in the women's 500 yard (457 meter) freestyle race.
The NCAA champion has sparked controversy and become a hate figure among conservatives, but statistics show little evidence that she performed any differently to other women, @iododds reports

How should you wish someone a ‘Happy Ramadan’? Find out more about familiar sayings and greetings
Many Muslims fast as a reminder to remain patient, learn self-discipline and to build an understanding of those that are suffering around the world
The fasting process is between dawn to sunset and is a sign of loyalty to the Islamic faith, which means that Muslims must abstain from eating and drinking, and yes, not even water
Before the fasting month begins, Muslims around the world prepare and wait for the arrival of Ramadan to be announced by the Saudi moon sighting committee or their local mosque
Ramadan is the ninth month in the Islamic calendar and changes every year in accordance with the moon 🌕

Mental health gets first mention

The report assessed the impacts of climate change on mental health for the first time, and linked rising heat, trauma from extreme events, and loss of livelihoods and culture.

Read the full story

Misinformation is a major problem in the US

Despite the fact that it is “unequivocal” that the climate crisis is human-caused, the IPCC says, misinformation and politicization of climate science has “created polarization in public and policy domains in North America”

Wildfires rising and creating feedback loops

Wildfires already generate one third of ecosystem carbon emissions, but these amounts will continue to rise, causing feedback loops as further carbon is released

Ukraine’s scientists forced to withdraw after Russian invasion

Ukrainian scientists involved in preparing the report were unable to complete work on the final details due to Russia’s invasion of the country

Africa has contributed the least emissions and is facing some of worst risks

The climate crisis will take a heavy toll on Africa’s ecosystems. Above 1.5C of warming, half of species on the continent are projected to lose more than 30 percent  of their population

Damage from flooding to increase 10-fold by 2100

Coastal flood damage represents an “existential threat” to communities and cultural heritage. Damage is projected to increase at least tenfold globally by 2100

The report describes how the climate crisis is a threat to human wellbeing and the health of the planet, and calls for urgent, transformative action to secure our future.
